This paper deals with the analysis of the trade-off between error and excess-rate exponents in variable-rate Slepian-Wolf coding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the use of coding techniques and algorithms (cs.CC), as well as the evaluation of performance metrics (cs.SI). The analysis involves the use of mathematical tools and techniques (cs.DS), and the paper also discusses the relationship between different types of coding schemes (cs.LG).
